image.altText: Sam kerr looks downcast

items.synopsis: The Matildas are up against European champions England in their Women's World Cup semifinal at Stadium Australia in Sydney, with both sides aiming for a spot in the final for the first time. Follow live.

title.children: 'We had three sitters in a row': Matildas bemoan missed opportunities

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Heartbreak for Australia and jubilation for England, into its first Women's World Cup final. The Lionesses were simply too good tonight. Absolute class on the ball, clinical with their finishing, resolute in defence, too fast, too strong. The Matildas had that Sam Kerr moment, which will live long in the memory, but will rue the chances they didn't take. Kerr had a couple of other great looks at 2-1 down, including a shanked volley that missed wide just a minute before England went down the other end and Alessia Russo put the match beyond doubt.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: The Matildas go down 3-1 to England in the World Cup semifinal

children.content: Heartbreak for Australia and jubilation for England, into its first Women's World Cup final.
The Lionesses were simply too good tonight. Absolute class on the ball, clinical with their finishing, resolute in defence, too fast, too strong.
The Matildas had that Sam Kerr moment, which will live long in the memory, but will rue the chances they didn't take.
Kerr had a couple of other great looks at 2-1 down, including a shanked volley that missed wide just a minute before England went down the other end and Alessia Russo put the match beyond doubt.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Once again the pace and skill of England's attackers does for the Matildas, with Lauren Hemp dribbling through the forward half and Alessia Russo ghosting away on the right, just waiting for the through ball. Eventually it came and she gathered on the edge of the box, firing low across Mackenzie Arnold. Just over a minute between Kerr's miss and that goal. Devastating for the Matildas, who need a miracle. We're not even expecting all that much stoppage time here.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: RUSSO MAKES IT 3-1 FOR ENGLAND!

children.content: Once again the pace and skill of England's attackers does for the Matildas, with Lauren Hemp dribbling through the forward half and Alessia Russo ghosting away on the right, just waiting for the through ball.
Eventually it came and she gathered on the edge of the box, firing low across Mackenzie Arnold.
Just over a minute between Kerr's miss and that goal. Devastating for the Matildas, who need a miracle.
We're not even expecting all that much stoppage time here.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The ball in behind puts Lauren Hemp alone against Ellie Carpenter and Clare Hunt, but Carpenter has two air-swings as she jostles with the England striker, who slots low and right to make it 2-1 to the Lionesses.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: ENGLAND RETAKES THE LEAD!!

children.content: The ball in behind puts Lauren Hemp alone against Ellie Carpenter and Clare Hunt, but Carpenter has two air-swings as she jostles with the England striker, who slots low and right to make it 2-1 to the Lionesses.
